  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Expanding Albaidha City and Suburbs Water Supply System</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Provide access to improved and sustainable water service for the people of Albaidha city.
- Reduce the incidents of cholera and AWD through providing water services and raising awareness.
- Make a breakthrough in urban water supply using dams as water source instead of focusing on diminished groundwater aquifers where unwise investments have been used for decades.
-Demonstrate how building trust and transparency between the service provider (AWSU) and its customers will improve the revenues and ensure the sustainability of the service.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The activity aims to mobilize the community towards controlling the shallow aquifer under Albaidha water and sanitation utility (AWSU) in collaboration with the community consumers committees that represent the beneficiaries. The activity will also expand the water system of Al Baidha city, provide solar pumping units, and build the capacity of AWSU.</narrative>
  </description>
